rComments: Her projects are pretty open ended ( you can basically do what ever you want within the guidelines) and she's open to practically any type of drawing style as long as you try. Her class really explores drawing as a practice and taking it helped me to find my own drawing 'style'. there was a lot of work though (weekly drawing assignments)
She is not good at teaching

Her feedback is usually given in class and during the critique, if any is provided. She's open minded about different approaches to her projects, so long as you hit the main points that she's provided for you. Her morning powerpoints, however, may put you to sleep.

Jen is very enthusiastic in teaching her subject and knows it well. Sometimes a bit confusing, but mostly because she is trying to explain complex concepts. Very encouraging, but also has high expectations. Hard marker. Has trouble splitting her attention between the class - you won't see her much in the woodshop.
